Sentencas: Ca-doping at the Y-site of Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+delta (YCBC) double perovskites is shown as an effective strategy to develop a highly efficient, stable, lanthanide-free cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The proposed Ca-doping has a beneficial influence on the structural stability, thermal expansion coefficient, electronic and ionic transport, and electrochemical properties of YCBC oxides.
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase stability and durability at evaluated temperature are greatly enhanced by Ca-doping.
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficients of Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+delta are calculated to be 18.1-18.7 x 10(-6) K-1.
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the conductivity is as high as 220 S cm(-1) for the Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo2O5+delta sample.
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Area specific resistances as low as 0.010, 0.018, 0.032, 0.068 and 0.142 Omega cm(2) at 850, 800, 750, 700 and 650 degrees C, respectively, are delivered by the Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo2O5+delta cathode in a La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolyte supported symmetric cell.
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of a full cell with the Y0.8Ca0.2BaCo2O5+delta/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta composite cathode are registered to be 1066, 841, 634 and 430 mW cm(-2) at 850, 800, 750 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All the results clearly demonstrate that Ca-doped Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+delta double perovskites are highly stable and effectively working candidate cathodes for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Effective Ca-doping in Y1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
